{"title":"Classified Powershift hub goes 12 speed for SRAM 2×12 gearing without a front derailleur","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/01/classified-powershift-hub-goes-12-speed-for-sram-2x12-gearing-without-a-front-derailleur/","date":1625130058000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Classified’s wireless electronic internal gear 2-speed Powershift rear hub makes the leap to 12 speeds with the addition of four new tightly-spaced SRAM-ready cassettes. Delivering all of the aero, straight chainline benefits of a 1x setup with the wide range and small gearing steps of a traditional road 2x drivetrain, the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=classified+powershift\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Classified Powershift system</a> can now work with SRAM 12sp road &amp; gravel drivetrains (and probably Campagnolo, too)!</p><h2>Classified Powershift 2x hub is now 12-speed SRAM compatible</h2><figure id=\"attachment_263569\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-263569\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x363/rscb20/ng:webp/ngcb20\" alt=\"Classified Powershift 2x internal gear hub now SRAM 12-speed compatible\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1200\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-297x223.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-800x600.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-120x90.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-768x576.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-1536x1152.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-696x522.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-1068x801.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-560x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-80x60.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-265x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 265w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x363/rscb20/ng:webp/ngcb20\" ezoid=\"0.7757791573724493\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-297x223.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-800x600.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-120x90.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-768x576.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-1536x1152.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-696x522.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-1068x801.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-560x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-80x60.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30140747/Classified-Powershift-2x-internal-gear-hub-now-SRAM-12-speed-compatible_Force-AXS-detail-265x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 265w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-263569\">c. Classified</figcaption></figure><p>The innovative <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=classified\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Classified Powershift system</a> delivers incredibly fast wireless electronic shifts inside the rear hub, <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/08/06/found-classified-wireless-internal-gear-hub-shifts-2x-range-on-your-1x-gravel-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">even under full power</a>, to eliminate the front derailleur without compromising on gearing. But the trick of the planetary reduction gear inside the rear hub has always been that it was limited to proprietary Classified cassettes that fit around the oversized hub shell. Classified makes what seems to be premium, fast-shifting one-piece steel cassettes, but they’ve been limited to 11-speed compatibility with four cassettes available. (<em>We’re testing a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/02/10/rose-backroad-x-classified-gravel-bike-offers-1x22-speed-electronic-drivetrain-at-lower-cost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Rose GRX Di2 2×11</a> setup right now, keep an eye for a full review next month.</em>)</p><p>Now four new 12-speed cassette options really open up the possibilities.</p><h3>Tech details</h3><figure id=\"attachment_249065\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-249065\"><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette.jpg\" alt=\"Classified Carbon Wheelsets, gravel &amp; all-road wheels with wireless 2x internal gear hub built-in,&nbsp;cassette\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Classified-Carbon-Wheelsets_gravel-all-road-wheels-with-wireless-2x-internal-gear-hub-built-in_machined-steel-cassette-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-249065\">Note: 11sp cassette shown</figcaption></figure><p>The four new 12-speed Classified cassettes are built just like the original 11sp variety, precisely machined in Europe from a single block of steel, and all share the same proprietary driver interface for the Powershift rear hub. That means all existing Powershift rear wheels can be upgraded to 12-speed simply by replacing the cassette.</p><p><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike.jpg\" alt=\"SRAM Red eTap AXS Max 36T medium cage rear derailleur, wider range gearing\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike.jpg 1500w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike.jpg 1500w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/SRAM-Red-eTap-AXS-Max-36T-medium-cage-rear-derailleur_on-bike-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Of course, it’s your own derailleur that shifts the chain across gears (while the 2x hub magic happens out of view inside the hub shell) so you’ll need a compatible 12-speed derailleur to make the switch. Classified only officially says that <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=SRAM+eTap+AXS\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">SRAM 12-speed shifting</a> is compatible, but we’ve seen pretty good cross-compatibility between SRAM road &amp; <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=campagnolo+12\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Campagnolo 12-speed</a> cassettes, so you likely could go for an Italian drivetrain too, if you want.</p><figur